<p>WEEP</p>
<p>lacrimare refers to the physical consequence of certain kinds of emotion of the mind, joyful or sorrowful, in the form of shedding tears.</p>
<p>plorare refers to a passionate expression of grief by wailing and crying.</p>
<p>flere partes of the passionless feeling denoted by lacrimare, but at the same time of the feeling of grief denoted by plorare.</p>
<p>lamentari refers to a higher degree of passionate lamentation than plorare.</p>
<p>eiaculare refers to a wailing interrupted by cries and sobs.</p>
